BofA Hires Former Goldman Electronic-Trading Salesman for Asia

-- B y   E l e n i   H i m a r a s
-- 
2011-09-16T01:57:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/bofa-hires-former-goldman-electronic-trading-salesman-for-asia.html
Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  has hired Kim Man Li, former head of Asian electronic trading sales at  Goldman
Sachs Group Inc. (GS) , as a director and head of product development
for Asia Pacific equity execution services in Hong Kong.  Li will join the bank’s Merrill Lynch unit, reporting to
Ryan Holsheimer, head of Asia Pacific equity execution services
in Hong Kong, and Roger Anerella, global head of electronic
trading in New York, according to an internal memo. Li will take
up his new role Oct. 3, said Mark Tsang, a Bank of America
spokesman in Hong Kong.  “Kim has been a pioneering figure in the electronic
trading space in Asia serving on numerous industry boards,”
Holsheimer said in the memo.  Li spent 11 years at Goldman Sachs, according to the memo.
He left the company in April as head of pan-Asian electronic
trading sales in  Hong Kong . Connie Ling, the spokeswoman for
Goldman Sachs in Hong Kong, declined to comment. Li could not be
reached for comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eleni Himaras in Hong Kong at 
 ehimaras@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
